items.title: Documentation for `name` param in get/delete transfer config very unclear

labels.name: api: bigquerydatatransfer
labels.description: Issues related to the BigQuery Data Transfer Service API.

labels.name: type: docs
labels.description: Improvement to the documentation for an API.

items.body:
The documentation describes that the first parameter to the get_transfer_config & delete_transfer_config methods should be "name". As far as I can tell, the name is the projects/foo/locations/foo/transferConfigs/unique-guid which is well, unique - how can this be obtained?! The only way you would have access to that unique ID is if you have access to the transfer config object in which case, you wouldn't need to get it!

The example shows that name can be generated from the classmethod, client.project_transfer_config_path.

But that classmethod wants "transfer_config" as a parameter which is circular and the documentation is [incredibly light](https://googleapis.dev/python/bigquerydatatransfer/latest/gapic/v1/api.html#google.cloud.bigquery_datatransfer_v1.DataTransferServiceClient.project_transfer_config_path).

When I try passing the object that I ultimately send to create_transfer_config, it doesn't work.

I can provide more detail if necessary but I'm hoping that someone is already aware of this and can either call out what i'm doing wrong and/or fix the documentation.

labels.name: type: feature request
labels.description: ‘Nice-to-have’ improvement, new feature or different behavior or design.

items.title: BigQuery Data Transfer Notifications API Enablement

labels.name: api: bigquerydatatransfer
labels.description: Issues related to the BigQuery Data Transfer Service API.

labels.name: triage me
labels.description: I really want to be triaged.

items.body:
I have been notified that the rollout for BigQuery Data Transfer Notifications API is completed. However, I'm still not able to set it up via `google.protobuf.json_format.ParseDict` & `bigquery_datatransfer_v1.types.TransferConfig()`. The error I got was:

```
Message type "google.cloud.bigquery.datatransfer.v1.TransferConfig" has no field named "notification_pubsub_topic".
 Available Fields(except extensions): ['name', 'destinationDatasetId', 'displayName', 'dataSourceId', 'params', 'schedule', 'scheduleOptions', 'dataRefreshWindowDays', 'disabled', 'updateTime', 'nextRunTime', 'state', 'userId', 'datasetRegion']
```

May I ask if there is any plan to add this field to `bigquery_datatransfer_v1.types.TransferConfig()`?

Thanks

items.body:
# My step：

1. Get Authorization code：I use this URL to get auth code 

       https://www.gstatic.com/bigquerydatatransfer/oauthz/auth?clientId=<id from list data sources>&scope=https://www.googleapis.com/auth/adwords%20https://www.googleapis.com/auth/bigquery

2. Create a service account with Project Owner
3. Execute sample code：

```
def run_quickstart():
    from google.cloud import bigquery_datatransfer_v1
    from google.protobuf.struct_pb2 import Struct

    client = bigquery_datatransfer_v1.DataTransferServiceClient()

    project = <project-id>
    parent = client.location_path(project, 'us')
    params = Struct()
    params.update({
        "customer_id": <customer-id>
    })

    transfer_config = {
        "destination_dataset_id": "test",
        "display_name": "test",
        "data_source_id": "adwords",
        "params": params
    }

    authorization_code = <authorization_code from step 1>
    response = client.create_transfer_config(parent, transfer_config, authorization_code)
    print(response)

if __name__ == '__main__':
    run_quickstart()
```

But I got the error：

The above exception was the direct cause of the following exception:

items.title: google-cloud-bigquery-datatransfer Readme code sample import does not work

labels.name: api: bigquerydatatransfer
labels.description: Issues related to the BigQuery Data Transfer Service API.

labels.name: type: docs
labels.description: Improvement to the documentation for an API.

items.body:
With google-cloud-bigquery-datatransfer 0.4.1, python3.7.5, this import works:

```
import google.cloud.bigquery_datatransfer_v1
```

but the readme at https://github.com/googleapis/google-cloud-python/blob/master/bigquery_datatransfer/README.rst contains this, which does not work for me:

```
from google.cloud.bigquery import datatransfer_v1
```

Is something off for me or is the Readme just wrong? Looks like the import I'm using matches the actual directory structure as well as the tests.
